 Art. 4.125.Purpose
The Central Inheritance Register is a computerised database whose purpose is to record the inheritance of the deceased's estate:
1¡ to allow, within the limits specified in this subtitle, consultation and communication to third parties by electronic means or, where appropriate, by post;
  a) information relating to documents determining the identity of persons entitled to an open succession;
  b) the identity of persons who have renounced or accepted an estate with the benefit of inventory;
  c) judicial measures taken in relation to the administration of an estate;
  [1 1¡ /1 to enable, within the limits specified in this subtitle, the status of heir to be established automatically, as referred to in Article 14, ¤ 1, paragraph 2, of the Royal Decree of 18 March 2020 introducing the Bank for Notarial Acts;]1
2¡ the processing, within the limits determined by Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC, of data recorded in the central register for purposes of general interest, and in particular for statistical and scientific purposes, or in order to improve the quality of the register.
